x4freetext: University of Wisconsin Lambshift
polarized ion source  and tandem accelerator
A beam of vector-polarized deuterons was momentum
analyzed and focused  through 1 x 3 mm beam-defining
slits into a scattering chamber
An evaporated 15 mg/cm2 lead target with an isotopic
enrichment of 99.5 % in 208Pb
An array of four rectangular detectors of 2 mm
depletion depth (system I) and four counter
telescopes (system II)

x4freetext: The errors include uncertainties from
counting statistics, the estimated effects of
uncertainties in the subtracted background, and the
possible effects of t20 and of Dt11. The errors for
the cross sections also include an uncertainty in
the relative data-detector solid angles of 2 % for
detection system I and  0 5 % for system II.
